sequenceDiagram
    actor User as Guest
    participant fe@{ "type": "boundary" } as Frontend
    participant API@{ "type": "control" } as API
    participant db@{ "type": "database" } as Database
    participant ms@{ "type": "control" } as Meilisearch

    Note over User,ms: Guest cancels their own PENDING booking

    User->>+fe: My Bookings → "Cancel" on a PENDING booking
    fe->>+API: PATCH /bookings/:id/cancel
    API->>API: verifyToken + checkBanned

    API->>+db: booking.findUnique(id)
    db-->>-API: booking or null

    alt Booking missing OR userId mismatch
        API-->>fe: 403 "You can only cancel your own bookings"
        fe-->>User: Show error
    else Owner confirmed
        alt status !== PENDING
            API-->>fe: 400 "Cannot cancel a booking that is already confirmed or completed"
            fe-->>User: Show error
        else status === PENDING
            API->>+db: booking.update(status = CANCELLED, include user+room)
            db-->>-API: cancelled booking
            API->>+ms: upsertBooking(toBookingDoc(cancelled))
            ms-->>-API: Re-indexed
            API-->>fe: 200 "Booking cancelled"
            fe-->>-User: Refresh My Bookings list
        end
    end

    Note over User,ms: CONFIRMED / COMPLETED cancellation goes through host or<br/>admin via PATCH /bookings/:id/status, not this endpoint.
